    "Model ↓ Reconstruction Time-stepping Compression rate Reconstruction Time-stepping Compression rate",
    "Results Table 1 presents the reconstruction and time-stepping errors for ENMA and baseline methods.",
    "These results highlight the robustness of ENMA across different grid sizes and datasets, in both 1D and 2D settings.",
    "While most baselines struggle as the grid becomes sparser, ENMA's encoding-decoding strategy consistently provides informative representations of the trajectories, even under limited observations.",
    "When the full grid is available (i.e., π = 100%), ENMA outperforms the baselines, reducing the reconstruction error by up to a factor of 3×."
